@adamcrussell Mouse exports 'inner' sub into the package namespace and it conflicts with inner exported by PDL, just un-import Mouse and the warning will go away.   
```
package  ExampleIterator;
use Mouse;
extends AI::MXNet::DataIter;
no Mouse;
use PDL;
```

@piiswrong @cjolivier01 since you tagged one another I'll tag you here as well 😜

Do you have any idea what's going on? if libgfortran3 is so critical for perf, why aren't we linking it in or including it? Why does it limit CPU utilization?

Seems like a major perf issue, unless the example does something really wrong.
